  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to Gmail**: Open your web browser and go to Gmail. Sign in to your account if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Access Google Account Settings**: \n   - Click on your profile picture or initial in the top right corner of the Gmail interface.\n   - Click on \"Manage your Google Account\" or \"Account\".\n\n3. **Navigate to Personal Info**: In the left sidebar, click on \"Personal info\".\n\n4. **Change Profile Picture**:\n   - Under the \"Profile\" section, you will see your profile picture.\n   - Click on your profile picture, and a window will open allowing you to change or remove it.\n\n5. **Remove the Profile Picture**:\n   - You may see options to change or delete the image. To remove the picture, look for an option that says \"Remove\" or an icon (like a trash can) to delete the picture.\n   - Confirm any prompts to finalize the removal.\n\n6. **Check Gmail**: Once you\u2019ve removed your picture, return to Gmail and refresh the page to see the changes reflected.\n\nYour profile may revert to the default avatar or show just your initials until you upload a new picture later.",
